DataElement.preferredName: Single Nucleotide Polymorphism Microarray Experiment Modified Partitioning Around Medoids Decision Rate java.lang.Double
DataElement.preferredDefinition: A variation of a single nucleotide at a specific location of the genome due to base substitution, present at an appreciable frequency between individuals of a single interbreeding population.:A piece of glass or plastic on which different samples have been affixed at separate locations in an ordered manner thus forming a microscopic array.  The samples are usually DNA fragments but may also be antibodies, other proteins, or tissues.:A set of actions and observations, performed to verify or falsify a hypothesis or research a causal relationship between phenomena._A classification algorithm based on the robust classification method called partitioning around medoids. MPAM includes terms in the objective function to penalize the small between-group distances. The resulting average silhouette width is a useful measure of classification quality.:A position, opinion, or judgment reached on an issue under consideration.:A measurement of degree, speed, or frequency relative to time._Generic value domain for a primitive java datatype that is a Double-precision floating point number (64-bit IEEE 7540).

Concepts.definition: A variation of a single nucleotide at a specific location of the genome due to base substitution, present at an appreciable frequency between individuals of a single interbreeding population.

A piece of glass or plastic on which different samples have been affixed at separate locations in an ordered manner thus forming a microscopic array.  The samples are usually DNA fragments but may also be antibodies, other proteins, or tissues.
A coordinated set of actions and observations designed to generate data, with the ultimate goal of discovery or hypothesis testing.

Concepts.definition: A classification algorithm based on the robust classification method called partitioning around medoids. MPAM includes terms in the objective function to penalize the small between-group distances. The resulting average silhouette width is a useful measure of classification quality.
